==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nubile
<hw>Nu"bile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nubilis</ets>, fr. <ets>nubere</ets> to marry: cf. F.
<ets>nubile</ets>. See <er>Nuptial</er>.]</ety> <def>Of an age suitable
for marriage; marriageable.</def> <rj><au>Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sexually attractive, sometimes used as a genteel
euphemism for <sig>having well-developed breasts</sig>; -- of a young
woman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nubility</ent>⟦br⟧
